metadata:

hadiths[13]{hadithnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
1067,"Narrated `Abdullah bin Mas`ud:The Prophet (ﷺ) recited Surat an-Najm (53) at Mecca and prostrated while reciting it and those who were with him did the same except an old man who took a handful of small stones or earth and lifted it to his forehead and said, ""This is sufficient for me."" Later on, I saw him killed as a non-believer",17,1,,,,,,ہم سے محمد بن بشار نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے غندر محمد بن جعفر نے بیان کیا کہا کہ ہم سے شعبہ نے بیان,1067,
1068,"Narrated Abu Huraira:On Fridays the Prophet (ﷺ) used to recite Alif Lam Mim Tanzil-As-Sajda (in the first rak`a) and Hal ata `alal-insani i.e. Surat ad-Dahr (LXXVI) (in the second rak`a), in the Fajr prayer",17,2,,,,,,ہم سے محمد بن یوسف فریابی نے بیان کیا، انہوں نے کہا کہ ہم سے سفیان ثوری نے بیان کیا، انہوں نے سعد بن,1068,
1069,"Narrated Ibn `Abbas:The prostration of Sa`d is not a compulsory one but I saw the Prophet (ﷺ) prostrating while reciting it",17,3,,,,,,ہم سے سلیمان بن حرب اور ابوالنعمان بن فضل نے بیان کیا، ان دونوں نے کہا کہ ہم سے حماد بن زید نے بیان ,1069,
1070,"Narrated `Abdullah bin Mas`ud:The Prophet (ﷺ) recited Surat-an-Najm (53) and prostrated while reciting it and all the people prostrated and a man amongst the people took a handful of stones or earth and raised it to his face and said, ""This is sufficient for me."" Later on I saw him killed as a non-believer",17,4,,,,,,ہم سے حفص بن عمر نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے شعبہ نے، ابواسحاق سے بیان کیا، ان سے اسود نے، ان سے عبدال,1070,
1071,"Narrated Ibn `Abbas:The Prophet (ﷺ) prostrated while reciting An-Najm and with him prostrated the Muslims, the pagans, the jinns, and all human beings",17,5,,,,,,ہم سے مسدد بن مسرہد نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے عبدالوارث نے بیان کیا، کہا ہم سے ایوب سختیانی نے بیان ,1071,
1072,"Narrated `Ata' bin Yasar:I asked Zaid bin Thabit about prostration on which he said that he had recited An-Najm before the Prophet, yet he (the Prophet) had not performed a prostration",17,6,,,,,,ہم سے سلیمان بن داؤد ابوالربیع نے بیان کیا، انہوں نے کہا کہ ہم سے اسماعیل بن جعفر نے بیان کیا، کہا ک,1072,
1073,"Narrated Zaid bin Thabit:I recited An-Najm before the Prophet, yet he did not perform a prostration",17,7,,,,,,ہم سے آدم بن ابی ایاس نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے ابن ابی ذئب نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے یزید بن عبدالل,1073,
1074,"Narrated Abu Salama:I saw Abu Huraira reciting Idha-Sama' un-Shaqqat and he prostrated during its recitation. I asked Abu Huraira, ""Didn't I see you prostrating?"" Abu Huraira said, ""Had I not seen the Prophet (ﷺ) prostrating, I would not have prostrated",17,8,,,,,,ہم سے مسلم بن ابراہیم اور معاذ بن فضالہ نے بیان کیا، انہوں نے کہا کہ ہم سے ہشام بن ابی عبداللہ دستوا,1074,
1075,"Narrated Ibn `Umar:When the Prophet (ﷺ) recited a Sura that contained the prostration he would prostrate and we would do the same and some of us (because of the heavy rush) could not find a place for prostration",17,9,,,,,,ہم سے مسدد بن مسرہد نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے یحییٰ بن سعید قطان نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے عبیداللہ ,1075,
1076,"Narrated Ibn `Umar:When the Prophet (ﷺ) recited Surat As-Sajda and we were with him, he would prostrate and we also would prostrate with him and some of us (because of the heavy rush) would not find a place (for our foreheads) to prostrate on",17,10,,,,,,ہم سے بشر بن آدم نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے علی بن مسہر نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہمیں عبیداللہ عمری نے خبر,1076,
1077,"Narrated Rabi`a:`Umar bin Al-Khattab recited Surat-an-Nahl on a Friday on the pulpit and when he reached the verse of Sajda he got down from the pulpit and prostrated and the people also prostrated. The next Friday `Umar bin Al-Khattab recited the same Sura and when he reached the verse of Sajda he said, ""O people! When we recite the verses of Sajda (during the sermon) whoever prostrates does the right thing, yet it is no sin for the one who does not prostrate."" And `Umar did not prostrate (that day). Added Ibn `Umar ""Allah has not made the prostration of recitation compulsory but if we wish we can do it",17,11,,,,,,ہم سے ابراہیم بن موسیٰ نے بیان کیا، انہوں نے کہا کہ ہمیں ہشام بن یوسف نے خبر دی اور انہیں ابن جریج ن,1077,
1078,"Narrated Abu Rafi`:I offered the `Isha' prayer behind Abu Huraira and he recited Idhas-Sama' Un-Shaqqat, and prostrated. I said, ""What is this?"" Abu Huraira said, ""I prostrated behind Abul-Qasim and I will do the same till I meet him",17,12,,,,,,ہم سے مسدد بن مسرہد نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ ہم سے معتمر بن سلیمان نے بیان کیا، کہا کہ میں نے اپنے باپ سے,1078,
1079,"Narrated Ibn `Umar.:Whenever the Prophet (ﷺ) recited the Sura which contained the prostration of recitation he used to prostrate and then we too, would prostrate and some of us did not find a place for prostration",17,13,,,,,,ہم سے صدقہ بن فضل نے بیان کیا، ان سے یحییٰ بن سعیدقطان نے بیان کیا، ان سے عبیداللہ نے، ان سے نافع نے,1079,
